Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.93,0:00:04.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Duel Carnival Semi-Finals have finally begun!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.65,0:00:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My opponent is Shark!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.94,0:00:10.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}However, Shark’s heart was manipulated by Tron, which made him believe I was responsible for his sister's injury!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.78,0:00:14.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Open your eyes, Shark! You were deceived!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.33,0:00:20.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.08,0:00:21.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shark’s Number!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.54,0:00:24.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.71,0:00:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck is a Number?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.04,0:00:27.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ain't never even heard of a Number before!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.84,0:00:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said Number… I've never seen that kind of thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.09,0:00:31.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.42,0:00:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What on Earth is that Monster?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.30,0:00:34.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that’s Shark’s Number.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.84,0:00:36.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks quite strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.55,0:00:38.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma…
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.68,0:00:44.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh~! What a fearsome Monster that is!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.48,0:00:50.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(619,528)}But it’s incredible. I have to get my hands on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.11,0:00:55.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though you said that, \Nyou must be off somewhere overjoyed at this sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.57,0:00:59.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But only for {\i1}now{\i0}, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.80,0:01:04.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Advance, advance, beyond the limits of your strength
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.14,0:01:10.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Come along with me and burn our flame of life
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.04,0:01:27.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hey, my friends, what scenery do you suppose
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.17,0:01:32.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}awaits us on the other side of this hill?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.63,0:01:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hey, my friends, let's climb it together
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.80,0:01:43.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's too soon for us to turn back now
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.06,0:01:48.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The time has come to combine\N together the power dwelling inside me
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.31,0:01:54.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Gotta release my Soul Drive
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.90,0:01:59.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Advance, advance, beyond the limits of your strength
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.12,0:02:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Come along with me and burn our flame of life
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.50,0:02:10.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Keep running, keep running, until you get there
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.75,0:02:16.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Once again, once again, keep those challenges coming
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.17,0:02:22.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My friends, keep on living in the here and now
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.55,0:02:28.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Keep pressing onward together no matter what happens
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.14,0:02:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(498,499)}"Number 62: Shark's Back!\N The Bonds Bounded By Bringin' it to 'Em!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.59,0:02:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! Shark Drake, attack Gogogo Ghost!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.85,0:02:45.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Depth Bite!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.11,0:02:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here comes another one, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.65,0:03:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(626,499)}I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.66,0:03:04.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(654,509)}I activate Shark Drake’s effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.66,0:03:09.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(662,507)}When it destroys a Monster by battle,\N by detaching one Overlay Unit,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.12,0:03:15.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(650,517)}it decreases the destroyed Gogogo Ghost’s Attack Power by 1000 points, and Special Summons it to Yuma’s field!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.96,0:03:20.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would he Summon Yuma’s Monster back to his field?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.47,0:03:24.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to attack once again!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.18,0:03:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You only have 900 Life left.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.89,0:03:30.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After I destroy Gogogo Ghost again, you're finished!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.48,0:03:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Shark Drake! Bite Gogogo Ghost and Yuma to pieces!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.69,0:03:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.32,0:03:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now Yuma will lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.70,0:03:46.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.74,0:03:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.21,0:03:57.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gogogo Ghost and Gogogo Golem have…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.96,0:03:59.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,…swapped!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.46,0:04:02.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look! Yuma's Life hasn't changed at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.09,0:04:07.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Why? Why would Gogogo Golem…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.43,0:04:09.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to Gogogo Ghost’s Monster Effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.68,0:04:15.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Gogogo Ghost is Special Summoned, it can Special Summon Gogogo Golem from the Graveyard as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.15,0:04:21.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Additionally, when this effect is used, Gogogo Ghost is changed to Defense Position!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.53,0:04:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, even if it was destroyed by Shark Drake, the damage I receive is still zero!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.20,0:04:32.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Desperate struggle for your life. I end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.37,0:04:34.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was amazing, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.25,0:04:35.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Beautiful tactics!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.87,0:04:38.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be thanks to Astral!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.63,0:04:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma is the one doing the fighting, so I won’t allow you to say something like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.34,0:04:47.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, do your best!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.80,0:04:51.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmmm, that wasn't half bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.01,0:04:54.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Faker: Numbers can only be defeated by Numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.73,0:05:01.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to win, Yuma Tsukumo has no choice but to Summon his own Number; the partition of that Original!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.48,0:05:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, use Hope! If you don't Summon Hope,\N there is no way we can win!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.41,0:05:15.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that! But I only have Gogogo Golem on my field. If I can just get another Level Four Monster…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.21,0:05:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.25,0:05:22.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darn it! It’s not a Monster Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.67,0:05:24.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t panic, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.59,0:05:29.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I'm panicking! If I don’t save him as soon as possible, he'll become Tron’s victim as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.43,0:05:38.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wake up, Shark! If you still have a shred of your true heart, try to remember our Duels!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.44,0:05:40.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our Duels?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.73,0:05:46.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s right! My first Duel ever with you was the battle that gambled mine and Tetsuo’s decks!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.95,0:05:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus you and I had a Tag Duel before, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.37,0:05:54.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Looks like our no-good Duelist improved a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.33,0:06:01.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was really excited when you said that to me. Because I could tell that our hearts had finally connected!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.21,0:06:07.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to protect this,\N you Dueled with Kaito, and that made he happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.64,0:06:16.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With Dueling, we've continuously strengthened our bonds! Isn't that right, Shark?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.56,0:06:19.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph! How boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.77,0:06:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea about things like friends or bonds,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.57,0:06:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but none of those things matter to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.94,0:06:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now the only thing supporting me\N is my heart of vengeance towards you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.58,0:06:37.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bravo! Nice, very nice! You're the best!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.91,0:06:40.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shark…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.29,0:06:45.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am here to defeat you in order to avenge my younger sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.09,0:06:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what’s {\i1}your{\i0} purpose here?\N Didn't you come here to {\i1}defeat{\i0} me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.51,0:06:54.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spare me from your almighty speech and just come at me! Your turn has already started!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.14,0:07:01.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know! If that’s what you want, I'll just have to deliver my thoughts through Dueling!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.81,0:07:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I switch Gogogo Golem from Defense Position to Attack Position!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.57,0:07:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I activate Quick-Play Magic, Golden Form!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.57,0:07:20.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card, when a Monster is switched from Defense Position to Attack Position, doubles that Monster's Attack Power until my next turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.92,0:07:28.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, how amazing this shiny sight is!\N It is indeed Golden Burning!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.88,0:07:33.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is Yuma thinking? Even if he managed to power-up Gogogo Golem…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.72,0:07:36.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To summarize, it still cannot defeat the Number!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.60,0:07:37.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.97,0:07:39.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.60,0:07:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But even if I can’t defeat his Number, I'll still charge from head-on and deliver my feelings to Shark!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.98,0:07:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s all I can do for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.77,0:07:54.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Gogogo Golem, attack Shark Drake! Great Cannon!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.46,0:08:07.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wake up, Shark! Hurry and get a hold of yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.13,0:08:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's a hit! Yuma’s super-heavy strike was effective! Now Yuma and Shark are tied at 900 Life!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.43,0:08:26.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Realizing he can't defeat my Number, he starts depleting my Life? But it ends now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.57,0:08:31.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one card and end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.03,0:08:34.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.36,0:08:39.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, this time I will finish you off completely...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.21,0:08:45.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...in order to avenge my sister and pay you back!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.59,0:08:50.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here it comes, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.42,0:08:56.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What’s that? What’s happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.93,0:08:58.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His body is glowing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.18,0:09:04.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I use Marine Biting Dragon - Shark Drake as Xyz Material to Chaos Xyz Change!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.86,0:09:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show yourself, Chaos Number 32!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.91,0:09:23.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Marine Biting Dragon - Shark Drake Vice!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.54,0:09:28.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What in the world?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.79,0:09:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ch…Chaos Number?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.88,0:09:34.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.26,0:09:39.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It finally appeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.39,0:09:41.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His Chaos Number…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.15,0:09:55.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chaos Number…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.82,0:09:59.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Under the current situation, we are overwhelmingly disadvantaged!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.78,0:10:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I go! I activate Shark Drake Vice’s Monster Effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.37,0:10:09.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By detaching one Overlay Unit, it Banishes one “Shark” Monster in the Graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.17,0:10:17.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I choose Spear Shark! And Gogogo Golem loses Attack Power equal to its 1600 Attack Power!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.59,0:10:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Spear Shark! Pierce it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.05,0:10:22.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.51,0:10:26.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma: I got it! I activate the Permanent Trap, Power Changer Barrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.02,0:10:31.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By decreasing Gogogo Golem’s Attack Power by 600...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.94,0:10:37.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...this card can negate Shark Drake Vice's effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.78,0:10:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He just blocked that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.61,0:10:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Shark Drake Vice still has Overlay Units left!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.45,0:10:44.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will strike again!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.83,0:10:45.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.74,0:10:48.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I will let you taste that once again!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.12,0:10:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By detaching an Overlay Unit, it Banishes a Monster in the Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.21,0:11:02.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I select Two-Head Shark! And Gogogo Golem’s Attack Power loses this card’s 1200 Attack Power!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.84,0:11:05.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ram him, Two-Head Shark!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.93,0:11:11.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I activate Power Changer Barrier’s effect again! It negates that Monster Effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.48,0:11:19.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s not over yet! I still have one Overlay Unit left!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.61,0:11:29.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I choose Shark Drake in my Graveyard! Letting Gogogo Golem’s Attack Power lose its 2800 Attack Power! Take this!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.45,0:11:31.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Defend it! Power Changer Barrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.63,0:11:43.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He finally managed to power up its Attack Power to 3600, but now he decreased it to 1800 with his own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.89,0:11:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, now Yuma only has 900 Life left. Does he even know what he’s doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.81,0:11:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s useless. The difference between Shark Drake Vice and Gogogo Golem’s Attack Power is 1000.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.19,0:11:58.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this attack connects, it’s over!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.53,0:12:04.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do it, Shark Drake Vice! Attack Gogogo Golem!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.70,0:12:08.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Depth Chaos Bite!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.79,0:12:12.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trap, activate! Half Unbreak!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.75,0:12:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to this effect, Gogogo Golem will not be destroyed, and my damage is halved!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.43,0:12:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What persistence. But when my next turn comes, you will fall into Hell completely!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.98,0:12:39.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one card and end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.98,0:12:43.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s right, it’s over when the next turn comes. Over for good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.24,0:12:51.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With that card I gave Ryoga as a present, Yuma Tsukumo will be eliminated!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.62,0:12:56.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Power Change Barrier saved us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.38,0:13:01.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We only have 400 Life left. Let’s settle it during this turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.84,0:13:02.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.67,0:13:08.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I…I…I believe in myself and my own deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.93,0:13:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna bring it to 'im!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.51,0:13:12.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.93,0:13:17.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it! I Summon Gagaga Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.78,0:13:27.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Overlay the Level Four Gagaga Magician and Gogogo Golem!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.87,0:13:32.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I build the Overlay Network with these two Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.62,0:13:33.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Xyz Summon!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.29,0:13:39.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time to show yourself, Number 39!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.79,0:13:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aspiring Emperor- Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.59,0:13:53.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You fool! Even if you managed to Summon Hope now, it can't defeat Shark Drake Vice with its 2500 Attack Power!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.72,0:13:57.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All you can do is pitifully struggle with\N the conviction of eventual defeat!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.69,0:14:01.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.07,0:14:07.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope won't die! Neither will your Number!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.45,0:14:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish to save you, and of course I don’t want lose either!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.58,0:14:18.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I desire to become the champion of the Duel Carnival, and finally settle the score with Tron and Dr. Faker.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.87,0:14:23.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But even if I win, I would feel worse losing you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.42,0:14:30.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, I… I will save you using whatever method necessary!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.64,0:14:34.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will release you from Tron’s curse!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.52,0:14:41.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I come, Shark! I attack Shark Drake Vice with Aspiring Emperor - Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.44,0:14:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope Sword Slash!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.28,0:14:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So in the end, you still run out of ideas and solely charge head on?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.03,0:14:54.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fight back! Depth Chaos Bite!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.79,0:15:06.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I detach one Overlay Unit, and activate Hope’s effect! It negates a Monster’s attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.97,0:15:12.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He actually negated Hope’s attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.05,0:15:13.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.18,0:15:18.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Permanent Trap, Bonds of Rival!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.77,0:15:28.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When my Monster’s attack is negated, I can equip this card to the battling Monster my opponent controls, and I gain that Monster’s control!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.40,0:15:32.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Im…impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.86,0:15:39.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Latch on to me, Shark Drake Vice! Leave Shark alone and come to my side!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.33,0:15:41.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma took Shark’s Number…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.87,0:15:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.33,0:15:45.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that way, Yuma will…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.48,0:16:06.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take it back, Shark! Your true heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.65,0:16:11.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yuma Tsukumo, I'll remember you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.86,0:16:13.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Obviously because we're friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.61,0:16:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't get involved with me anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.53,0:16:17.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Something about revenge...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.20,0:16:18.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We'll settle things in the Finals!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.16,0:16:21.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don’t want to see that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.41,0:16:31.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Y-Yuma... It wasn't Yuma... who hurt my little sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.97,0:16:37.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tron was the one who hurt my sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.81,0:16:42.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been controlled by the Number this entire time!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.69,0:16:45.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.48,0:16:46.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shark!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.61,0:16:52.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.70,0:16:56.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yuma sure is suffering, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.78,0:16:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tron!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.12,0:17:03.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, it’ll be his turn to be manipulated by the Number. What will you do, Ryoga?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.96,0:17:08.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has redeemed you from agony, \Nand now he is suffering in your place.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.51,0:17:13.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.84,0:17:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tron: You wish to save him, yes? Assuming you are one of his friends, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.81,0:17:21.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.64,0:17:32.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems you have recalled it. That’s right, just use that Trap Card. Use Medallion Catastrophe!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.69,0:17:35.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Medallion…Catastrophe…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.19,0:17:37.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma...! Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.28,0:17:39.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.16,0:17:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s alright! Pretty soon Ryoga will come and save you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.33,0:17:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tron…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.70,0:17:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to your effort of stealing Shark Drake Vice, that Trap Card on Ryoga’s field, Medallion Catastrophe, can be activated now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.55,0:18:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the opponent gains control of your Monster, this card can destroy all Monsters with Attack Power equal to or lower than that Monster's.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.76,0:18:08.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, both Shark Drake Vice and Aspiring Emperor - Hope will be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.10,0:18:09.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,WHAT?! Even Hope too…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.73,0:18:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tron(to Shark): That way Yuma can escape from the curse of the Number, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.94,0:18:21.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the total of the destroyed Monsters’ Attack Power, in other words, 5300 damage, will be inflicted to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.04,0:18:32.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That way victory will be yours. I gave that card to you because I knew something like this would happen. A sure-kill Trap, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.30,0:18:37.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Hope is destroyed, then Astral, too…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.92,0:18:40.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is…is there any other way?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.60,0:18:51.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right! Traplin! By releasing one Permanent Trap on the field, it can be Special Summoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.35,0:18:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I use this effect to destroy Bonds of Rival…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.82,0:19:00.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s right, Shark Drake Vice would return to Shark, and Hope and I will be saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.28,0:19:06.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he will be controlled by the Number, no, Tron again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.12,0:19:15.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s right. Alright, which side will you choose? Ryoga or Astral?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.55,0:19:18.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tron!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.59,0:19:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You decide, Yuma.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.34,0:19:22.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.55,0:19:30.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is nothing more I can do under these circumstances. This is your Duel. You will do the thinking and make the decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.31,0:19:36.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't... I can't choose between you and Shark!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.15,0:19:41.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shark: Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.61,0:19:46.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don’t save him as soon as possible, he will only suffer more and more.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.99,0:19:52.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So do it, Ryoga. Activate Medallion Catastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.25,0:19:58.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be it Shark Drake Vice, Aspiring Emperor - Hope, along with Yuma Tsukumo... Bury them together!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.09,0:20:02.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.05,0:20:17.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't choose... I just can't choose! Because to me, both you and Shark are very important... friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.61,0:20:19.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.07,0:20:27.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That set card is the one I set from the very beginning. I…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.70,0:20:31.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Quick-Play Magic, Marine Snow Seal!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.41,0:20:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Banish Shark Drake Vice!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.47,0:20:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will receive 1000 points of damage as the price!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.73,0:20:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shark!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.78,0:21:09.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The…The winner is…Contestant Yuma Tsukumo…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.24,0:21:12.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.70,0:21:19.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get a hold of yourself, Shark! Hey!\N In order to save us, you…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.75,0:21:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, during the Duel, I could always hear your voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.22,0:21:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That heart of yours that never gives up, your "Bring it to 'Em", has saved me from Tron.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.76,0:21:39.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you. Also, please, defeat Tron! You can definitely do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.69,0:21:43.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that’s friendship and bonds?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.36,0:21:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just when will you get enough out of getting in my way, Yuma!?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.24,0:21:56.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh well. I will finish off Yuma Tsukumo nice and slowly later... with my own hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.29,0:22:01.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is the one who saved my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.46,0:22:07.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. I didn't win this Duel. He gave victory to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.97,0:22:10.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Additionally, you were entrusted his feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.22,0:22:14.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, I'll inherit all of Shark's feelings and definitely win!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.81,0:22:17.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna bring it to 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.50,0:22:25.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We stand tall, until we have victory in our grasp
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.89,0:22:31.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Move on ahead, speeding up our throbbing beats
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.90,0:22:41.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Listen boys and girls, here's the secret to boys and girls like you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.36,0:22:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're really just so spontaneous, wild as can be
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.24,0:22:47.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I bet you didn't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.78,0:22:50.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You might be a handful, but what's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.37,0:22:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Be up to no good, but learn for real
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.00,0:22:58.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go the unpredictable route and shuffle your cards with a goal in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.25,0:23:03.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whenever you feel like you've lost your way, just take a minute to close your eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.51,0:23:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Shout "stop!" with all you've got, and there's your boundary line.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.39,0:23:15.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We stand tall, until we have victory in our grasp
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.69,0:23:21.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We won't just stop here, not when we don't want to have any regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.19,0:23:26.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if we get hurt, we can't just hesitate now
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.49,0:23:31.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We won't just give up, not when our future's a lot brighter than our today
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.87,0:23:37.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Seriousness... It'll only make us keep fighting even harder
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.33,0:23:42.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We'll always get as fascinated as we want, and we'll fight on every day
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.74,0:23:53.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Using the power of the Heraldry Beasts, Tron is pushing Kaito into a corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.49,0:23:56.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Kaito has strategies that may be superior to his.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.91,0:23:58.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Yu-Gi-Oh! ZeXal!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.74,0:24:01.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"A Horrifying Dark Strategy!\N Tron's True Colors Revealed!?"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.96,0:24:04.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Tron's mask is...!
